PRD
├─ 01_Overview.md
│   ├─ App Name: Glass Journal
│   ├─ One-liner: A minimalist mood and journal app with modern glassy design.
│   ├─ Goal: Help users quickly capture their daily feelings and thoughts in a beautiful, calming interface.
│   ├─ Platforms: Android, iOS (Web optional later)
│
├─ 02_UserPersona.md
│   ├─ Persona 1
│   │   ├─ Name: Sarah, 24, university student
│   │   ├─ Needs: Wants to track emotions and thoughts daily to reflect on mental health.
│   │   ├─ Pain Points: Other apps feel too cluttered, confusing, or take too long to log an entry.
│   │   ├─ Goals: Use a simple, fast, and aesthetic app that motivates her to check in daily.
│   ├─ Persona 2
│   │   ├─ Name: Amir, 29, young professional
│   │   ├─ Needs: Wants a lightweight journaling tool to note stress or gratitude moments during workdays.
│   │   ├─ Pain Points: Forgets to journal, doesn’t want a heavy app with too many features.
│   │   ├─ Goals: Stay consistent by having an easy, visually appealing journaling habit.
│
├─ 03_UserFlow.md
│   ├─ Step 1: Open app (see welcome screen with glassy header)
│   ├─ Step 2: Login/Register OR continue as Guest
│   ├─ Step 3: Tap “+” button to add mood/journal entry
│   ├─ Step 4: Choose mood icon + optional text note
│   ├─ Step 5: Save → entry shows in timeline (list) and calendar
│   ├─ Step 6: User can browse old entries, edit, or delete
│   ├─ Step 7: Exit app or set reminder for tomorrow
│
├─ 04_Features.md
│   ├─ Must Have (MVP)
│   │   ├─ Add a mood entry (select from icons + text)
│   │   ├─ View saved entries in a list
│   │   ├─ Edit or delete an entry
│   │   ├─ Glass-style UI (using expo-glass-effect on iOS, edge-to-edge on Android)
│   ├─ Nice to Have (later)
│   │   ├─ Calendar view of moods
│   │   ├─ Graph of mood trends over time
│   │   ├─ Daily reminder notification
│   │   ├─ Cloud sync for multiple devices
│
└─ 05_TechNotes.md
    ├─ Framework: Expo SDK 54 + React Native
    ├─ Styling Library: React Native Paper + expo-glass-effect
    ├─ Language: TypeScript
    ├─ Data Storage: AsyncStorage (local MVP), future Firebase or Supabase for sync
    └─ Future plans: Push Notifications, OTA Updates, Analytics, Predictive Back gesture support on Android

Tabs
├─ Home
│   ├─ Purpose: Daily mood check-in and quick entry
│   ├─ UI ideas:
│   │   ├─ “+” Floating Action Button to add new entry
│   │   ├─ Glassy top bar showing today’s date & mood summary
│   │   ├─ List of recent entries (horizontal cards or timeline)
│
├─ Journal
│   ├─ Purpose: View all past entries (calendar & timeline)
│   ├─ UI ideas:
│   │   ├─ Calendar at top → tap a date to see entries
│   │   ├─ Filter by mood type (Happy, Sad, Calm, etc.)
│   │   ├─ Edge-to-edge scroll with blurred background
│
├─ Insights
│   ├─ Purpose: Reflect on your patterns & emotional trends
│   ├─ UI ideas:
│   │   ├─ Mood frequency chart (pie or bar chart)
│   │   ├─ Longest positive streak or average mood score
│   │   ├─ Quotes or reflections generated by AI (future)
│
└─ Profile
    ├─ Purpose: Personalize experience & settings
    ├─ UI ideas:
    │   ├─ Avatar, name, and short “About me” note
    │   ├─ Theme toggle (Light/Glass/Dark)
    │   ├─ Reminder settings
    │   ├─ Data backup / sync option
